    ----------------------------------
    Create primer paramerter files for Primer 3
    ----------------------------------
     review manual here: https://primer3.org/manual.html
    ----------------------------------
     Primer3 requires a specially formatted input file. The file must be formatted like this:
    SEQUENCE_ID=YOUR.SEQ.ID
    SEQUENCE_TEMPLATE=NUCELOTIDES.WITH.NO.SPACES.ON.SAME.LINE
    PRIMER_TASK=generic
    PRIMER_PICK_LEFT_PRIMER=3
    PRIMER_PICK_RIGHT_PRIMER=3
    PRIMER_OPT_SIZE=18
    PRIMER_MIN_SIZE=15
    PRIMER_MAX_SIZE=21
    PRIMER_MAX_NS_ACCEPTED=1
    PRIMER_PRODUCT_SIZE_RANGE=75-150
    P3_FILE_FLAG=1
    PRIMER_EXPLAIN_FLAG=1
    =
    


```bash
%%bash
cd ../
# For putative AOX gene PGEN_.00g108770
# Use heredoc to create Primer3 parameters file - For AOX gene PGEN_.00g108770
# this script creates the perameters file to use with primer3
# NOTE: the sequence must be one line with no spaces
# i.e. in notepadd++.. highlight and Cntrl+J and find/replace spaces for no space
cat << EOF > Documents/Bioinformatics/qPCR_primer_design/Alternate_oxidase/blah.txt
SEQUENCE_ID=PGEN_.00g108770
SEQUENCE_
PRIMER_TASK=generic
PRIMER_PICK_LEFT_PRIMER=3
PRIMER_PICK_RIGHT_PRIMER=3
PRIMER_OPT_SIZE=18
PRIMER_MIN_SIZE=15
PRIMER_MAX_SIZE=21
PRIMER_MAX_NS_ACCEPTED=1
PRIMER_PRODUCT_SIZE_RANGE=75-150
P3_FILE_FLAG=1
PRIMER_EXPLAIN_FLAG=1
PRIMER_THERMODYNAMIC_PARAMETERS_PATH=C:/Users/samjg/primer3/src/primer3_config/
=
EOF
```
